This has been reported a few times from customers. It seems that from different nodes in a Confluence Data Center instance you can kick off concurrent synchronisation for the same directory. This causes a range of problems.

It seems that the synchronisation is done around directory attributes:

{noformat}
    public boolean isSynchronising(final long synchronisableDirectoryId) throws DirectoryNotFoundException
    {
        final Directory directory = findDirectoryById(synchronisableDirectoryId);
        final String isSynchronising = directory.getAttributes().get(SynchronisableDirectoryProperties.IS_SYNCHRONISING);
        return isSynchronising != null && Boolean.valueOf(isSynchronising);
    }
{noformat}

And these attributes are local hashmaps (see com.atlassian.crowd.model.directory.DirectoryImpl.attributes) and therefore there is no cluster wide synchronisation.

